}}'''''Clues'o'''''' is a 1985 [[Murder mystery game|murder mystery]] [[video game]] developed and published by [[Imperial Software]].

==Plot and gameplay==
''Clues'o''' is a game in which the player is a French detective. They must find out who killed Major Fawcett by asking characters around the map.<ref name="Imagine25"/><ref name=":0">{{Cite book |last=Campbell |first=Keith |url=https://archive.org/details/Computer_Video_Games_Issue_045_1985-07_EMAP_Publishing_GB/page/n85/mode/2up |title=Computer & Video Games - Issue 045 |publisher=[[Computer & Video Games]] |year=1985 |editor-last=Metcalls |editor-first=Tim |page=86 |chapter=Clues'o'}}</ref> 

==Reception==
<!-- Graphics -->
The graphics of ''Clues'o''' had mixed reception. D J Robinson reviewed the game for ''[[Imagine (AD&D magazine)|Imagine]]'' magazine and stated that the game had "well drawn" graphics and "adequate" text.<ref name="Imagine25">{{cite journal | last = Robinson |first = D J | title =Game Reviews | type = review | journal = [[Imagine (game magazine)|Imagine]] | issue = 25| pages =45 | publisher = TSR Hobbies (UK), Ltd. |date=April 1985}}</ref> However, Keith Campbell of ''[[Computer and Video Games|Computer & Video Games]]'' criticized the overall presentation as "very ordinary".<ref name=":0" />

